      <p>Turning on multi-user mode is the easy part. The work that makes it hold is everything around it: installing and scanning with the <code>QuickBooks Database Server Manager</code> on the host, getting Windows folder permissions and the firewall right so the <code>H101</code>, <code>H202</code>, <code>H303</code>, and <code>H505</code> errors don&rsquo;t return, configuring role permissions so each person sees only what they should, and confirming the books reconcile before more than one person starts working in the file. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, licensing, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
